caption: Pizza is outstanding!!!!!!  Some of the best pizza in Brooklyn...hands down! Drove far to get it..but always worth it!

Hands down, my go to place in NY. Right next to Pratt, so when I went I ate here a lot! I brought my Mom here when she visited and she still talks about this place. People who work here have been there forever and super kind.  What else is there to say? They make the best Hawaiian  Really sad they close on Sundays though because sundays are great pizza days ;)

My experience was via Door Dash delivery and was ordered via the Luigi’s website. I have tried quite a few places in the Clinton Hill area and this is BY FAR the best in terms of the gravy and dough flavor. If you like your pizza darker/crisp, ask for it well-done, which can be chosen as an option online when checking out. I am a native NYer/Long Islander— giving an honest pizza opinion. Thank you Luigi’s staff!

Why would you want Luigi's pizza?  Pros:  Low price for high quality ingredients Being serenaded by Mozart playing on an old radio when you step in to pickup... Near the G train Clinton/Washington. Moderately fast service. Moderate price. 4.5-Star Rated Pizza (that's amazing)  Cons:  No seating. Sometimes pizza is a bit oily. No delivery. They don't sell swag.  Highlights:  If you like a solid white pizza but are ok to take a loss on margarita, then this will be perfect for you.  They often offer two kinds of mushroom pizzas by the slice. Fresh or canned.  Across from Pratt campus, which has great park bench seating amongst their beautiful commons areas.

Stopped by Luigi's because the Love of My Life suggested a different pizza joint, but I suggested Luigi's for several reason's. 1 - the place that was suggested had fallen by way side and I did not want to spend tons of money for fallen from grace food.  If you know what I mean?  2 - I have always enjoyed Luigi's but I do not get a chance to visit as much as I would like to, even though I do not need the extra calories, fat, guilt and so-on, because it is off the beaten track.  Located in lovely Clinton Hill and we live in lovely Prospect Heights.  But I digress and do not want to.  Particularly, when it comes to food.  Great food at that! Luigi's pizza pies and sicilians slices are New York City old skool good.  They make the grade because they want to make a good meal and it shows in the number of guests on the constant of picking up, mid-morning, noon and nite even. The two guys that were on duty Monday evening 1/7/19,  were smiling, and engaging as ever. Making pies again, and again and again. The stuff is really good.  It is reflective of the good stuff that is possible within the five cool and funky boroughs that make up New York City proper. Luigi's is good food for any and every reason.  You simply must stop by and check out their fiddles to go! Thank you.

I used to go to this pizzeria all the time a few years back. Therefore, I decided to go since I was always left satisfied. When I arrived to the spot, I noticed some changes and a "grade pending" sign. I wanted to know what the sign meant and when I asked I was given an unbelievable excuse so I was a bit skeptical. However,  I still proceeded to order pizza. Despite the sign, I was still excited to dig in to this delicious slice because I had been craving pizza for awhile. As I took a bite of the pizza I was immediately displeased. I thought that maybe it would get better, but I was wrong. I ate the slice ,but was very upset that it did not satisfy my craving. It was MEDIOCRE and I felt like I wasted unnecessary calories. Needless to say, I will not be returning. You win some. You lose some.
